	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yo.. <br>I only used one handed till I was into my 40s.&nbsp;&nbsp;Being that my Paladin was my first character I didnt have much money to get anything else.  I aquired a Mithril 2 hander at about 42 or 43 cant remember. With a 0 skill in 2hs, I couldnt do anything.  I went to the Dreadlands and got a good group and asked if I could practice they said I could.  With our enchanter hasting me and the haste on the Mitril I went from a 5 skill to 180 in a night.. <br>The moral of this story?<br>Don't worry about your 2hs skill too much unless you have a weapon you want to use.  I have since aquired my Wurmslayer and FBSS.. so until I get another 2hs I want to use.. Im back to bashing.<br><br>I also noted that you have 3 chars.. all in the mid teens.  I would suggest that you concentrate on one.. you will have much more success.. the ability to go in and get my alts, and friends stuff with no problems is nice indeed.<br><br>Lord Sartoran Battleskar, Commander of Chaos<br>Answering to no one since conception<br>Level 49 Paladin on The Tribunal<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan 31 00:05:40 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Sartoran Battleskar<br>52nd Cavalier of Brell<br>The Tribunal---&gt; Vis Veres</td></tr>
