<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101223866191516></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101223866191516><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=101223866191516>RE: suggestions</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=101223866191516#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83710><span id=Scholar>jcasetnl</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>153 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 28th 12:24 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In my opinion don't worry about wis items, or even resist gear.&nbsp;&nbsp;Focus intently on your armor class first and foremost.  After that focus on hit point items that you can stick in your ear and finger slots.  And always keep your weapons up to date.  At 19 I recommend the BABS.  It's cheap but will more than get the job done.  I still use one at 40 as my alt weapon but they are obtainable at your level.  And when you get to 20 and the damage cap is gone this thing starts to hit like a monster.<br><br>As far as running faster this is one area where I wish VI would change their ways.  Access to speed enhancing items doesn't really exist until about the mid-40s with things like Journeyman's boots or Tboots, and then later on with horses and the run speed alt exp option.  But by the time you get to about level 30 you will really start getting tired of running around at a snail's pace.  <br><br>The other option is sow potions which go for about 100p for ten shots.  Each shot lasts about an hour.  At level 19 I would never have spent my money on this but at 40 they have become worth it.  Once you get to about level 30 the majority of the bad guys con green to you in many zones.  So you get a little less careful.  But there's always those one or two mobs that can give you trouble.  If you happen to run into these guys sometimes the only option is to run for it as they'll resist everything in your arsenal or hit you too fast to get a spell off.  Now you have just lost two or three hours of exp grinding.  Not to metion the boring and possibly expensive corpse run.<br><br>Finally on the bow, this is mainly a matter of preferance I spose but I pull exclusively with Cease now.  The range is a little shorter but it's never been a problem.  It's cheap mana wise and I save a lot of room in my inventory.  It also keeps my weight down.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
