	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Burgen...I like the last name!<br><br>There is one piece of armor, in my opinion, that you should focus on, and work HARD to get ASAP.&nbsp;&nbsp;Out of all of my current armor:<br><br>Custom Scaled Knight's Helm<br>Queen's Carapace<br>Deepwater Greaves<br>Scaled Knight Vambraces<br>Crystal Chitin Gauntlets<br>Deepwater Boots<br>Bracer of Benevolence<br>Deepwater Bracer<br>Dragontooth Choker<br>etc...<br><br>I do not own a single piece that has been more important or beneficial than this one piece...<br><br>The Deepwater Helm!!<br><br>I don't wear it all the time anymore, but when I solo, I still pull it out and put it on.  I was recently in Karnor's Castle soloing the undead from the moat and I even had to click off the Uber Cleric Buff Spell Aegolism because it didn't provide the benefits that having this helm on did.  I was in a group just last night in Dragon Nec and we got wiped out when a rat gated.  After rezzes, Cleric was OOM, everyone was sitting around with 2 bubs of health, and the chance of a wandering Rat was High.  I pulled the Deepwater Hlem out of my bag and in minutes the Enchanter was full health.  Soon the Main Tank was too. Then I was.  By this time the Cleric could chime in with heals, but there was no need! He continued to med while I healed the Rogue!  Granted, it's boring as heck to cast Daring over and over and over again, but it sure is a handy dandy item.<br><br>I highly recommend it and it should cost somewhere around 1k plat. Maybe less if you get a good deal. You won't be sorry.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
