	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dal was my first character.&nbsp;&nbsp;I regret it, a little.  I'm so used to being able to tank AND cast that I can barely play any other class.  I almost made my first character a warrior to get the hang of EQ, but. *shrug*<br><br>He's still my favorite after 39 levels of pallyism.  But, if you're willing to stick it out, (especially the patronizing remarks directed our way until about 9), a paladin can be a very enjoyable starting class.<br><br>I just recently started being able to main heal for the group (and that scares the druid friend I have).  Lay on Hands is a great panic button, though.<br><br>Paladins are a fairly difficult class to start as.  *shrug*  I managed it, even though I've had my fair share of times when I've thought &quot;That's it, I'm deleting Dal.&quot;  But I've stuck it out, and being a Defender has been rewarding and fun.  I can solo, I can heal, I can damage sponge.  *grin*  I can nuke undead, at times, too.  It's fun, but a little difficult to get started.<br><br>I hope that helped.<br>&nbsp;<br>Dalantia Dragonet<br>Beloved Cavalier of Catwalkk Silverpaw, 51st Rank<br>Fennin Ro<br>Second Foundation</td></tr>
