	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'd give consideration to the Erudite paladin as well.&nbsp;&nbsp;Like the high elf, the low strength is only an annoyance early on, and not much of one at that.  You get high INT as well as very good WIS, so learning things is a snap.  Get to around sixth level, and hit the Warrens -  It's a fantastic &quot;lowbie&quot; zone: lots of kobolds, lots of loot, very little competition.  You can rack up exp and cash faster here than anyplace I've seen for levels 6-22.<br><br>The lack of infravision is a non-issue if you have a good graphics card, and that's the only real disadvantage to the race.  They're also fun to role-play.<br><br>Good luck deciding.  Should you decide on an Erudite, and start him on the Nameless, look up my &quot;son&quot; Bejaizen.  He's always happy to lend a hand to the beginning Erudite Paladin.<br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>35th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
