	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings all,<br><br>I recently completed the last Drop Item (the tainted sword) for my epic and thought I'd share some information about faction when you are working on your own flaming Defender Sword.<br><br>For anyone working on their Defender, you know that you interact with an Erudite Paladin, Reklon Gnallen, in Erudin. He is on Deepwater Knight faction. Despite all my faction work in my earlier days with the various Paladin guilds throughout Norrath, my DW Knight faction was always the worst. I started out Dubious and worked my way to Indifferent, while all the other guilds were either Warmly or Ally.<br><br>I got the tainted sword from the Keeper of Tombs in the Hole.&nbsp;&nbsp;You have to turn this sword into Reklon Gnallen along with some purified water so he can &quot;purify&quot; the sword.  I DID THIS STEP WITH INDIFFERENT FACTION.  He gave me back the Gleaming Crested Sword just like he was supposed to.<br><br>I then handed him the Gleaming Crested Sword, Gleaming Crested Shield and Gleaming Crested Breastplate.  Crossed my fingers and clicked the &quot;Give&quot; button.  I DID THIS WITH INDIFFERENT FACTION.  He handed me the &quot;Mark of Atonement&quot; just like he was supposed to.<br><br>All I have left now is the turn-in in the Plane of Air for the Fiery Avenger, and then the turn-in in the Plane of Fear for the Fiery Defender!<br><br>So don't let anyone tell you differently. I am here to say that INDIFFERENT faction worked just fine for me with the Deepwater Knights and Reklon Gnallen...even though I had heard through the grapevine anything from &quot;must be ally&quot; to &quot;at least be Kindly&quot;.  But NO ONE told me it was okay with Indifferent Faction.  Well, it is, and I am proof!<br><br>I'll post a further update as soon as I can make it to the Plane of Air's 4th island!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br></td></