	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was really hoping to use my bow a lot more but as it is it basically collects dust in the bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;The one and only use I found for it was  pulling.  <br><br>Even to that end, I've found something that works as well if not better: Cease.  It doesn't have the range of some bows but it only costs 15 mana.  No more lugging around a bow and arrows.  <br><br>Believe it or not the very short effect stun will often keep the mob off your back in the same way that using a longer range bow does due to added running space.  And if you find it's not enough, just move up to desist or stun.  Either way, paladins in general are typically full mana at the end of a fight whereas everyone else is totally drained so the mana cost ussually isn't that big a deal.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
